cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a novel method to incorporate corpus-level discourse information into language modelling. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper introduces a late fusion approach to a recurrent language model based on long short-term memory units (LSTM). 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a method to improve language modelling, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses LSTM units, which are a type of neural network. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category as there is no mention of sound or audio in the paper.
